This is Perl module DBIx::Rico.

INSTALLATION

DBIx::Rico installation is straightforward. If your CPAN shell is set
up, you should just be able to do

    % cpan DBIx::Rico

Download it, unpack it, then build it as per the usual:

    % perl Makefile.PL
    % make && make test

Then install it:

    % make install

DOCUMENTATION

DBIx::Rico documentation is available as in POD. So you can do:

    % perldoc DBIx::Rico

to read the documentation online with your favorite pager.

